# Ignore loose per-run artifacts at the root of repro/logs/.
# Per the four-step disambiguator protocol (Plan 02 Task 1), each
# step's `bash run_5x.sh ...` produces these at the root, and they
# are then `cp`'d into a stepN/ subdirectory for permanent archival.
# The next step's invocation `rm -f`'s them before re-running.
# Tracking them at the root would create churn on every disambiguator
# run. The canonical evidence lives in stepN/ subdirectories (those
# are checked in explicitly).
run-*-sse.log
run-*-uvicorn.stderr
summary.jsonl
